</ul>

<p>Always verify the current qualification status of a specific vehicle before purchasing, as the eligible vehicle list is updated quarterly.</p>

<h2 id="how-to-claim">How to Claim EV Incentives</h2>

<h3>Claiming the Federal Tax Credit</h3>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Verify vehicle eligibility.</strong> Check the IRS and Department of Energy websites to confirm the specific make, model, and trim qualifies for the credit.</li>
  <li><strong>Purchase or lease from a qualified dealer.</strong> The vehicle must be purchased from a licensed dealer (not a private party) to qualify for the new vehicle credit.</li>
  <li><strong>Obtain the seller's report.</strong> The dealer must submit a time-of-sale report to the IRS confirming the vehicle qualifies and the credit amount.</li>
  <li><strong>File IRS Form 8936</strong> with your federal tax return to claim the credit, or elect to transfer the credit to the dealer at the time of purchase for an immediate price reduction.</li>
</ol>

